{
  "info": {
    "name": "Monobase",
    "description": "API collection for the Monobase backend: auth (better-auth), api-gateway (REST + GraphQL proxy), and graphql (NestJS code-first).\n\nArchitecture:\n- gateway ({{gateway_url}}) is the single entry point for browser traffic. It proxies /api/auth/* to the auth service, exposes /api/v1/* REST routes, and forwards POST /graphql/v1 into the graphql service over a Redis/TCP microservice transport.\n- auth ({{auth_url}}) and graphql ({{graphql_url}}) are reachable directly for debugging only.\n\nGraphQL versioning: the GraphQL endpoint is path-versioned to mirror the REST surface — POST /graphql/v1 (gateway) and ws://localhost:3002/graphql/v1 (subscriptions) are the only supported paths.\n\nSession handling: Postman keeps cookies automatically across a session — better-auth sets the session cookie on sign-in and the same cookie is then sent on get-session, admin/* and authed /graphql/v1 calls.\n\nOrigin header: better-auth enforces an Origin check on authenticated state-changing requests. The collection-level pre-request script sets Origin: {{gateway_url}} on every request.\n\nGraphQL admin/users: the @repo/graphql service exposes a CRUD resolver over the shared user table from @repo/db. Mutations write directly to Postgres — they bypass better-auth password hashing and account-row creation, so users created via createOneUser cannot sign in via email/password until a password is set through the auth API.\n\nFiles upload: two-phase flow against MinIO. createUploadUrl returns a pre-signed PUT URL and a fileKey, the client PUTs the binary directly to MinIO, then calls registerUpload(fileKey) to flip the DB row to completed. Both mutations require an authenticated session and tie the file to the caller via uploadedBy.\n\nSubscriptions: createdUser / updatedOneUser / deletedOneUser are GraphQL subscriptions and require WebSocket transport. Use a Postman WebSocket request to ws://localhost:3002/graphql/v1 to test them — they aren't included as collection items because Postman models WS separately.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// better-auth requires Origin header on authenticated state-changing requests",
          "// (CSRF protection). Always send the gateway URL as Origin.",
          "const gatewayUrl = pm.collectionVariables.get('gateway_url');",
          "if (gatewayUrl) {",
          "  pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'Origin', value: gatewayUrl });",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
